description:
&lt;p&gt;Sussex Partnership is about the people. The people we work for, the people we work with and the people we want to become. We want to create the right job for you that not only provides a service but works with your interests.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research&lt;/strong&gt; – Are you looking to further or start your research? We have Research Assistants embedded within teams and have access to leading edge technology to support you with this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education&lt;/strong&gt; – Are you interested in taking students on placement or getting involved with teaching? We have strong links with Brighton and Sussex Medical School.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support &lt;/strong&gt;– Are you looking for opportunities to work flexibly or work in teams that understand and support each other? We appreciate how caring our staff are and recognize the importance of caring about you too.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is seeking a consultant psychiatrist to join Rowan Ward, Meadowfield Hospital, Worthing. This is a post covering an acute working age ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is being advertised as full time. However, please get in touch if you are interested in the position but want to work different hours. We can discuss how this role can work for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of a friendly and supportive multidisciplinary ward team that consists of other Consultants, Nurse’s, Occupational Therapists, Psychologists and more. The Trust strives to maximize clinical time for doctors so you will benefit from an assigned 0.5 WTE of direct admin support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also work with other community services in West Sussex including local Crisis team, Assessment and Treatment Services, Early Intervention and Assertive Outreach community services. There are separate community services for patients with a suspected or confirmed diagnosis of dementia and older persons.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of a Trust wide consultant network where there are opportunities to liaise with colleagues in other acute wards throughout the Trust and develop peer networks. You will also see consultant peers weekly at the local academic programme, at regular division meetings in the locality and at clinical governance meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust operates a QI methodology which is encouraged to be used by all staff. This post is one example of the commitment of the Trust to develop better provision and capacity for Langley Green hospital and the families and carers using the service. There are also opportunities to use SPA time for teaching or clinical and other basic research through Sussex University and Brighton and Sussex Medical School.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sussex Partnership is committed to participation, meaning that we involve patients and their carers and supporters, in service decision-making and planning. You will be expected to contribute to this shared value and to support the functioning of this service in the delivery of its participation strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not decided yet or want to discuss your individual interests in working at Sussex Partnership then please pick up the phone and talk to us! We want to hear your thoughts and ideas on how our jobs can work for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Claire TannerJob titleClinical DirectorEmail addressClaire.Tanner@sussexpartnership.nhs.ukTelephone number07710977985&lt;/p&gt;
